Interview Answer (30 seconds)
=========================================================

"Variadic templates, introduced in C++11, allow a template to accept
any number of template arguments using parameter packs. They eliminate
the need for writing multiple overloaded functions, provide compile-time
type safety, and are heavily used in the STL. Common examples include
std::make_shared, std::make_unique, std::tuple, std::thread, and
emplace functions. In C++17, fold expressions simplify many recursive
variadic template implementations."

